column8:
フルレンジ・インサレーションを採用した画期的なフーディ。
保温性と伸縮性に加えて優れた通気性を提供し、動いたり止まったりを繰り返す山での激しい有酸素運動でも継続的な着用が可能。

【メンズ・ナノエア・フーディ】
いったん腕を通したら、壮大なリード、雪しぶきのなかでのビレイ、頂上への同時登攀、そして下降まで脱ぐ必要がありません。
フリースの快適さと通気性にインサレーションのプロテクションと保温性を組み合わせたナノエアはテクニカル・インサレーションの新標準を打ち立てます。
軽量ながら丈夫で悪天候に対応するDWR（耐久性撥水）加工済みのリップストップ・ナイロン100％製シェルと平織りの裏地のあいだに濡れても保温性を維持するフルレンジ・インサレーションをはさんだ素材は格別な伸縮性と通気性を提供。
このうえなくソフトで滑らかな肌触りとメカニカル・ストレッチによりベースレイヤーの上でアスレチックなフィットを実現し、無制限の動きやすさを発揮します。
肌寒いビレイや極寒の状況では軽量なシェルの下で保温効果が一気に上昇。
伸縮性を備えたすっきりとしたフードは頭に直接かぶるデザインですが、小さめのヘルメットの上にもぴったりとフィットします。
ハーネス着用時もじゃまにならない配置のハンドウォーマーポケットと両胸のポケットはかさばらないジッパー付き。
フロントジッパーはストームフラップとジッパーガレージを備え、伸縮性素材で縁取った袖口と２つの調節ポイントを備えたドローコード付きの裾が温かさを閉じ込めます。

■軽量ながら丈夫なリップストップ・ナイロン製のシェルと平織りの裏地はメカニカル・ストレッチと非常に優れた通気性を提供。DWR（耐久性撥水）加工済み
■保温性と伸縮性を備えた画期的な60グラム・フルレンジ・インサレーションをシェルと裏地のあいだにはさんだ結果、無制限の動きやすさと優れた通気性（40CFM）を提供するジャケット
■両脇に施したナノ・パフの特徴的なレンガ型キルトパターンと、体の各部に沿ったキルトパターンがフィット感と耐久性を向上
■ジャケットのジッパーを上げたままでも着脱しやすい縁取り付きの伸縮性フード
■フロントジッパーは内側に撥水性を備えたストームフラップ付き。あごへのあたりが快適なジッパーガレージ付き
■ハンドウォーマーポケットが２つとチェストポケットが２つ。いずれもハーネスやバックパック着用時もかさばらないジッパーと縁取り付き
■伸縮性素材で縁取った袖口と２つの調節ポイントを備えたドローコード付きの裾が温かさを逃さない
■シェル：メカニカル・ストレッチ織りの1.3オンス・20デニール・リップストップ・ナイロン100％。DWR（耐久性撥水）加工済み。裏地：メカニカル・ストレッチ平織りの２オンス・50デニール・ナイロン100％。DWR加工済み。インサレーション：ポリエステル100％の60グラム・フルレンジ・ストレッチ・インサレーション
■385 g (13.6 oz)
■ベトナム製

column8:
タウンユースに保温性を発揮する軽量カジュアルダウンジャケット。
軽量Ricoジャケットはリラックスした都会派な仕上がり、高品質なダウンフィルは爽やかな日にも気軽に羽織れます。
Bastナイロン表面素材は軽量で耐久性のあるマットな色合いのタフタに由来し、防風機能も高く、柔らかでコットンのような風合いです。
DWR仕上げにより耐湿機能も追加。本体には保温性のある750フィルパワーグースダウン、肩部にはCoreloft合成繊維インシュレーションを採用して熱を閉じ込め、スクエアキルティングでダウンの偏りを抑えて、ラインをきれいに見せます。

【細身】
RicoのラインはArc’teryxのミニマリストな見映えに反映しています。
フルジップフロントとスタンドアップ カラー、両サイドの軽量フリース パネルにより、見た目もきれいにスリムフィット、シェルの下にも簡単にレイヤリングできます。
Arc’teryxのこだわりである動きやすさに立体構造を取り入れています。
隠しジッパー付きのハンドポケットは小さい基本装備を収納。
このスマートな混合素材、すっきりデザイン、うごきやすさにより、Ricoは街着にも万能な一着になります。

【Arc'teryx ダウン構造】
ダウン仕上げの違い - パフォーマンスを最大限に生かしたミニマリストデザインは、快適の域を広げた革新性とコンディションにより最高レベルの技術を確立しました。
効果的かつ軽量で耐久性も兼ね備えて普段着としても活躍。
・優れた軽暖値
・体の芯までしっかりと熱を閉じ込めます
・高圧縮性

【Arc'teryx フィットガイド - アスレチックフィット】
「Arc’teryx のスタンダード」フィットとも言える、身体構造に基づいた形とガセットを採用した複雑なパターンにより、可動性を強化いて、余分な容量を抑えています。
リラックスフィットよりも細身で、ベースレイヤー、軽量フリース ミッドレイヤー、さらに合成繊維またはダウンフィルミッドレイヤーのスペースも確保。

【サイズ】S, M
【重量】350 g / 12.3 oz
【特徴】
・Moisture-resistant outer face fabric
・Insulated
・Lightweight
・Compressible and packable
・Arc'teryx Nu water repellent treatment
・Square quilting minimizes down shift
・Light fleece side panels with stretch woven overlay
・Athletic fit for a slimmer more flattering profile
・Articulated sleeves
・Insulated stand up collar
・Full front zip with insulated wind flap
・Two hand pockets with hidden zippers
・Internal zippered pocket
【素材】
・750 fill European goose down
・Classic 100 Micro Velour Small Grid
・Bast - 100% nylon taffeta with DWR finish
【お手入れ】
・手洗いコース温水（30°C）で洗濯機洗い。
・柔軟剤不可。
・横型洗濯機推奨（縦型洗濯機の場合は洗濯ネットを使用すること）。
・すすぎ2回
・テニスボールまたは「ソックボール」を入れて低温でタンブラー乾燥。乾燥時間は3時間以上かかる場合があります。
・アイロン不可。
・スペースに余裕がある乾燥した場所にしまいましょう。

──【メーカーカタログより】──
Love the look of cinematic pilots, or were you once a pilot yourself our CWU pilot jacket boasts the same silhouette/trims of the original CWU 45/p. Stay cozy with the 100 percent nylon outer shell and quilted nylon liner on our CWU pilot jacket. Keep your belongings secure in our signature alpha utility/pencil pocket and battle the elements with our CWU pilot jacket's lined cargo pockets/front zipper closure with storm flap. Alpha Industries was founded on the belief that the U.S. Armed forces deserved protective clothing that was of superior quality and delivered outstanding defense against extreme climate conditions. From our start in October 1959, the U.S. Department of defense (dod) awarded alpha contracts to produce jackets for American service members, including iconic styles such as the n-3b parka and the ma-1 flight jacket. Alpha grew rapidly during the 1960s, as the Vietnam war led to a substantial increase in dod production contracts. Lessons learned from intense battlefield experience also led to new technological advances in fabric and the manufacturing process. Alpha soon began producing infantry jackets, including the iconic m-65 field coat made legendary during the Vietnam war. Today, Alpha Industries is known around the world for its high-quality, military-inspired outerwear. We continue to produce the classic military silhouettes that are core to our heritage, as well as modern innovations in style and function. Our top sellers include the ma-1 flight jacket, the m-65 field coat, the slim-fit n-3b parka and the g-1 leather bomber. But no matter the jacket, coat, or bomber, one thing will always hold true, the alpha three-bar label will always represent the superior quality that we base our very reputation on.

──【メーカーカタログより】──
Lighten things up with this contemporary variation of our classic MA-1 flight jacket. The bomber features a trans-nylon, water-resistant shell with nylon lining. The nylon-web oxygen tab with contrast stitching is a unique detail that pays homage to the original mil-spec MA-1 that had the tab so pilots could clip their masks to it. Alpha Industries was founded on the belief that the U.S. armed forces deserved protective clothing that was of superior quality and delivered outstanding defense against extreme climate conditions. From our start in October 1959, the U.S. Department of Defense (DOD) awarded Alpha contracts to produce jackets for American service members, including iconic styles such as the N-3B parka and the MA-1 flight jacket. Alpha grew rapidly during the 1960s, as the Vietnam War led to a substantial increase in DOD production contracts. Lessons learned from intense battlefield experience also led to new technological advances in fabric and the manufacturing process. Alpha soon began producing infantry jackets, including the iconic M-65 Field Coat made legendary during the Vietnam War. Today, Alpha Industries is known around the world for its high-quality, military-inspired outerwear. We continue to produce the classic military silhouettes that are core to our heritage, as well as modern innovations in style and function. Our top sellers include the MA-1 flight jacket, the M-65 field coat, the Slim-Fit N-3B parka and the G-1 leather bomber. But no matter the jacket, coat, or bomber, one thing will always hold true, the Alpha three-bar label will always represent the superior quality that we base our very reputation on.

──【メーカーカタログより】──
Alpha Industries was founded on the belief that the U.S. armed forces deserved protective clothing that was of superior quality and delivered outstanding defense against extreme climate conditions. From our start in October 1959, the U.S. Department of Defense (DOD) awarded Alpha contracts to produce jackets for American service members, including iconic styles such as the N-3B parka and the MA-1 flight jacket. Alpha grew rapidly during the 1960s, as the Vietnam War led to a substantial increase in DOD production contracts. Lessons learned from intense battlefield experience also led to new technological advances in fabric and the manufacturing process. Alpha soon began producing infantry jackets, including the iconic M-65 Field Coat made legendary during the Vietnam War. Today, Alpha Industries is known around the world for its high-quality, military-inspired outerwear. We continue to produce the classic military silhouettes that are core to our heritage, as well as modern innovations in style and function. Our top sellers include the MA-1 flight jacket, the M-65 field coat, the Slim-Fit N-3B parka and the G-1 leather bomber. But no matter the jacket, coat, or bomber, one thing will always hold true, the Alpha three-bar label will always represent the superior quality that we base our very reputation on.

──【メーカーカタログより】──
Lighten things up with this contemporary variation of our classic MA-1 flight jacket. The bomber features a trans-nylon, water-resistant shell with nylon lining. The nylon-web oxygen tab with contrast stitching is a unique detail that pays homage to the original mil-spec MA-1 that had the tab so pilots could clip their masks to it. Alpha Industries was founded on the belief that the U.S. armed forces deserved protective clothing that was of superior quality and delivered outstanding defense against extreme climate conditions. From our start in October 1959, the U.S. Department of Defense (DOD) awarded Alpha contracts to produce jackets for American service members, including iconic styles such as the N-3B parka and the MA-1 flight jacket. Alpha grew rapidly during the 1960s, as the Vietnam War led to a substantial increase in DOD production contracts. Lessons learned from intense battlefield experience also led to new technological advances in fabric and the manufacturing process. Alpha soon began producing infantry jackets, including the iconic M-65 Field Coat made legendary during the Vietnam War. Today, Alpha Industries is known around the world for its high-quality, military-inspired outerwear. We continue to produce the classic military silhouettes that are core to our heritage, as well as modern innovations in style and function. Our top sellers include the MA-1 flight jacket, the M-65 field coat, the Slim-Fit N-3B parka and the G-1 leather bomber. But no matter the jacket, coat, or bomber, one thing will always hold true, the Alpha three-bar label will always represent the superior quality that we base our very reputation on.

──【メーカーカタログより】──
Alpha Industries was founded on the belief that the U.S. armed forces deserved protective clothing that was of superior quality and delivered outstanding defense against extreme climate conditions. From our start in October 1959, the U.S. Department of Defense (DOD) awarded Alpha contracts to produce jackets for American service members, including iconic styles such as the N-3B parka and the MA-1 flight jacket. Alpha grew rapidly during the 1960s, as the Vietnam War led to a substantial increase in DOD production contracts. Lessons learned from intense battlefield experience also led to new technological advances in fabric and the manufacturing process. Alpha soon began producing infantry jackets, including the iconic M-65 Field Coat made legendary during the Vietnam War. Today, Alpha Industries is known around the world for its high-quality, military-inspired outerwear. We continue to produce the classic military silhouettes that are core to our heritage, as well as modern innovations in style and function. Our top sellers include the MA-1 flight jacket, the M-65 field coat, the Slim-Fit N-3B parka and the G-1 leather bomber. But no matter the jacket, coat, or bomber, one thing will always hold true, the Alpha three-bar label will always represent the superior quality that we base our very reputation on.
